The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Israel stun Russia to make semis
                                                   Israel stun Russia to make semis
                      
	Tel Aviv: Israel reached the Davis Cup semi-finals for the first time on Saturday after Andy Ram and Jonathan Erlich gave them an unbeatable 3-0 lead over Russia in their World Group quarter final here.         
	The experienced pairing of Ram and Erlich thrilled the home supporters to beat Russias Marat Safin and Igor Kunitsyn 6-3, 6-4, 6-7, 4-6, 6-4 in the doubles.         
	Everybody has dreams but there are some you dont allow yourself to have and beating Russia 3-0 was just like that... but we have done it, Erlich said.         
	In Marebella, Fernando Verdasco and Feliciano Lopez handed champions Spain a 2-1 lead in their Davis Cup World Group quarter final after beating German doubles pair Nicolas Kiefer and Mischa Zverev 6-3, 7-6, 6-7, 6-3 Saturday.         
	The victory on a second day of scorching heat in Marbella gives Spain the advantage ahead of Sundays two reverse singles.         
	Meanwhile, Bob and Mike Bryan kept United Statess hopes of reaching the Davis Cup semi-finals alive with a 6-3, 6-1, 6-3 win over Croatian pair Roko Karanusic and Lovro Zovko in the doubles on Saturday in Porec.         
	The Bryan brothers had to win the doubles to extend the tie into a third day after the United States came off second best in Fridays epic singles matches, which had both gone to five sets.         
	In Ostrava, Tomas Berdych and Radek Stepanek handed the Czech Republic a 2-1 lead over 2008 runners-up Argentina in their quarter-final tie. (Reuters)                                                                                                                       
